class Solution {
public:
    ListNode *detectCycle(ListNode *head) {
        ListNode *slow = head;
        ListNode *fast = head;
        while(fast != NULL && fast->next != NULL){
            slow = slow->next;
            fast = fast->next->next;
            if(slow == fast){
                slow = head;
                while(slow != fast){
                    slow = slow->next;
                    fast = fast->next;
                }
                return slow;
            }
        }
        return NULL;
    }
};

Interview Explanation
Step 1

"First, I detect whether a cycle exists using slow and fast pointers."

Step 2

"If both pointers meet, I move the slow pointer back to the head."

Step 3

"Now both pointers move one step at a time."

Step 4

"The node where they meet again is the starting point of the cycle."

Easy Notes
1. Detect cycle.

2. Slow = Head.

3. Fast = Meeting Point.

4. Move both one step.

5. Meeting point = Start of Cycle.
